# API Debugging Runbook (Beginner)

## 1) What to collect before you troubleshoot
When a user reports an API problem, I collect:
- What they were trying to do (goal)
- Endpoint (URL), HTTP method (GET/POST/etc.)
- Timestamp (and timezone)
- Status code (e.g., 404, 401, 500)
- Request headers (especially Authorization)
- Request body (if any)
- Response body (error message)
- Any request id / trace id (if the API provides it)

## 2) A simple mental model (picture)
User → sends request → API → returns response

